.TH YAML_NEXT_EVENT 3 "2026-06-30" "libyaml 0.1.0" "libyaml library"
.SH NAME
yaml_next_event, yaml_has_pending_events, yaml_event_count \- event queue operations
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <yaml.h>
.PP
.BI "int yaml_next_event(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ", yaml_event_t *" event ");"
.BI "int yaml_has_pending_events(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.BI "size_t yaml_event_count(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR yaml_next_event ()
dequeues the next event from the context's event queue.
The event structure is filled with the event type and data.
.PP
.BR yaml_has_pending_events ()
returns 1 if there are events waiting to be dequeued, 0 otherwise.
.PP
.BR yaml_event_count ()
returns the number of events currently in the queue.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.BR yaml_next_event ()
returns 1 if an event was dequeued, 0 if the queue is empty.
.SH EVENT TYPES
The
.I yaml_event_t
structure contains:
.TP
.I type
One of YAML_EVENT_STREAM_START, YAML_EVENT_STREAM_END,
YAML_EVENT_DOCUMENT_START, YAML_EVENT_DOCUMENT_END,
YAML_EVENT_MAPPING_START, YAML_EVENT_MAPPING_END,
YAML_EVENT_SEQUENCE_START, YAML_EVENT_SEQUENCE_END,
YAML_EVENT_SCALAR, YAML_EVENT_ALIAS, YAML_EVENT_ERROR.
.TP
.I data
Union containing event-specific data (scalar value, tag, anchor, etc.).
.SH THREAD SAFETY
Not thread-safe. Use from a single thread at a time.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yaml_create (3),
.BR yaml_feed_input (3),
.BR yaml_event_t (3)
